<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="93" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 290.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-07-08"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 8, 1862.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> As inquiry may be made of you as to the
                            approbation by this government of a treaty recently concluded by Mr.
                            Corwin with the government of Mexico, by one of the stipulations of
                            which a sum of money was to be paid to that government, I have to inform
                            you that the instrument was submitted to the Senate, but the Committee
                            on Foreign Relations of that body has reported adversely thereon. It is
                            not probable, therefore, that at this session at least the Senate will
                            advise and consent to the ratification of the treaty.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                            <p rend="center">[Same to W. L. Dayton, No. 177.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>